args: Ohmigosh, the food at that cafe was\nto DIE for!
(I need to find a way to clear things up\nwhile we're on this date.)
Hey, about that thing you thought was\na proposal...
Do you think that cafe will still be there\nwhen we have kids? Ooo, I wanna bring\nthem there so bad!
And then while we're eating, we can tell\nthem how Mommy and Daddy had their\nFIRST DATE there! Tee hee!
(Urgh... She's making this so hard to\nbring up...)
Hey Luccy, can we stop at the tailor next?
Huh? Weren't you gonna look at clothes?
Nope. I'm here for fabric to MAKE clothes.
Yep! Accessories, dolls, all kinds of things.
(I just realized I don't actually know that\nmuch about her.)
I want to make some baby clothes.\nWhich do you prefer: floral or plaid?
Hmm. Personally, I'd go for something\na little more exciting, like—wait, whose\nbabies, exactly?
Oh, goodness me! Are you two expecting?
Congratulations to you. Here, please take\nboth, on the house!
Wow! Look, Luccy! Now I can make clothes\nfor TWO little ones!
(I need to put my foot down, and fast!)
Listen up, Chelsea! We need to talk about\nour relationship, okay?
Luccy, you silly boy. Don't make a scene.
You know what? I should make new outfits\nfor Mama and Papa, too. I'll take these\nfabrics as well, please!
Um, Luccy? I'm going to go pick\nsome flowers.
Tell you what though, she's unexpectedly\ndevoted to her family. Makin' clothes\nfor her parents and everything... Wait.
I don't know where I'd go, though.\nI don't have any family...
Who are Mama and Papa then...?
What the hell are you guys doing?!
What's it to ya? You her boyfriend\nor somethin'?
You're right. I meant FUTURE husband!
Jeez, shut up already. I dunno what's up\nwith you two, but unless you wanna taste\nthese hands, I'd get lost.
Sorry, but we're actually in the middle\nof a date.
Yeah? Well your face is about to be\ndatin' these fists! Hraaagh!
Look out, Luccy! And you, let GO of me!
Watch your step, kid. If you're not careful,\nthis pretty little bird's gonna have a\nbroken wing. Capiche?
Now take what's comin' to ya!
Look on the bright side, gorgeous.\nWe just saved ya from marryin' a loser!\nHa ha ha!
YOU'RE IN FOR IT NOW! Let me GO!
Quit squirmin', dammit! You want both\narms broken?!
I have to save my Luccy...
I'll be fine. Man, you sure kicked the crap\noutta those goons.
Love can be dangerous when threatened.\nHee!
Hey! You think you can just walk away?!
Uh oh, Luccy, they're getting back up!
Guess we'll have to set 'em straight\nfor good.
We're gonna be great parents, huh?\nC'mon, Luccy!
I'm glad it all worked out, but still... Ow.
I got you some medicine, and bandages\ntoo. Gimme oooone second, and I'll have\nyou all fixed up.
(She's an oddball, but she's got a\ngood heart.)
(Which is exactly why I have to clear\nthings up with her ASAP.)
You know, you've saved me twice now.
Huh? When was the first time?
Back when we first met! I think about it\nevery morning... And every night, too!\nTee hee!
What? You saved ME when we first met.\nI was fightin' those fiends.
No, before that. You helped search\nfor my Mama and Papa.
We met on a mountain, right?\nAnd you said you had no family...
...I see. I was sure our meeting was fate...
But for you, it was just... *sob*
What was that all about?\nDid we meet before that...?
